---

This project includes code derived from Nix.rs (https://github.com/griff/Nix.rs)
by Brian Olsen, which is triple-licensed under EUPL-1.2, LGPL-2.1-or-later, and MIT.
Harmonia uses the MIT license option for all imported Nix.rs code.

Specifically, the following crates contain code derived from Nix.rs:
- harmonia-store-engine (from nixrs core)
- harmonia-nar (from nixrs archive)
- harmonia-protocol (from nixrs wire protocol)
- harmonia-protocol-derive (from nixrs-derive)
- harmonia-daemon (from nixrs daemon)

Individual source files from Nix.rs contain SPDX headers referencing the upstream
commit hash for provenance tracking.
